---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import boldOpinionLogo from "../img/bold_opinion.jpeg";
import weekendBlindingLights from "../img/the-weeknd-blinding-lights.jpg";
import PNotes from "../components/PNotes.astro";
---

<p-slide class="center">
  <h1 style="margin-block-end: 1rem;">
    🚨 <span class="cover-all">ALERT!</span> 🚨
  </h1>
  <p-fragment
    ><h3 class="cover-all" style="margin-block: 1rem;">Bold opinion here!</h3>
    <Image
      src={boldOpinionLogo}
      alt="bold opinion logo"
      class="alter-image-size"
      style="--image-start-size: 4em"
    />
  </p-fragment>
</p-slide>
<p-slide autoplay class="cover-internal">
  <h1>Universal Design</h1>
  <p-fragment
    ><Image
      src={weekendBlindingLights}
      alt="the weekend blinding lights"
      class="alter-image-size"
      style="--image-start-size: 6em"
    /></p-fragment
  >
</p-slide>
<p-slide class="center">
  <h3>What is Universal Design? 🤔</h3>
  <p-fragment
    ><h4 class="cover-all">
      The main goal is to create a single solution that works for everyone
    </h4></p-fragment
  >
  <PNotes>
    <p>
      - It originates from architecture with the goal of creating environments
      and products usable by all people, to the greatest extent possible,
      without the need for adaptation or specialized design
    </p>
    <p>
      - On the web, it inspired the core principles of WCAG: a site with good
      contrast and semantic markup is "universally" more accessible to people
      with low vision and screen reader users.
    </p>
  </PNotes>
</p-slide>
<p-slide class="center">
  <h3>The Illusion of the <span class="cover-all">"Universal" User</span></h3>
  <h4 p-fragment>Some examples 👉</h4>
  <PNotes>
    The concept of "everyone" is an abstraction. In the digital world, the
    "universal" user often aligns with a specific profile: Western, accustomed
    to certain technological conventions, and possessing a particular mental
    model.
  </PNotes>
</p-slide>
<p-slide>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <span style="font-size: 5rem"
        >📌 Iconography: <span p-fragment>💾</span></span
      >
      <p p-fragment style="margin-block-start: 2rem;font-size: 3rem">
        The 'save' icon is not universal, <span class="cover-all"
          >it's generational</span
        >
      </p>
    </li>
    <li style="margin-block-start: 2rem;" p-fragment>
      <span style="font-size: 5rem"
        >📌 Workflows: <span p-fragment>🛠️</span></span
      >
      <p p-fragment style="margin-block-start: 2rem;font-size: 3rem">
        A <span class="cover-all">"universal" checkout process</span> that prioritizes
        credit cards fails in contexts where other methods are the norm
      </p>
    </li>
  </ul>
</p-slide>
<p-slide class="cover-internal">
  <h1 style="margin-block-end: 2rem;">How can we do better?</h1>
  <span p-fragment>∘ ∘ ∘ ( °ヮ° ) ?</span>
</p-slide>
<p-slide class="center">
  <h3 style="margin: 0">🥁 Welcome to 🥁</h3>
  <h3 p-fragment class="cover-all">Plural Design: The Adaptive Approach</h3>
</p-slide>
<p-slide>
  <p>- Don't look for ONE solution for everyone</p>
  <p p-fragment>
    - Create a <span class="cover-all">flexible system</span> that recognizes diverse
    mental models and presents the most appropriate solution
  </p>
</p-slide>
<p-slide class="center">
  <h3 class="cover-all" style="margin-block: 1rem;">End Bold opinion</h3>
  <Image
    src={boldOpinionLogo}
    alt="bold opinion logo"
    class="alter-image-size"
    style="--image-start-size: 4em"
  />
  <h2 class="cover-all" style="margin-block-start: 2rem;">ദ്ദി ˉ͈̀꒳ˉ͈́ )✧</h2>
</p-slide>
